Justice and Correctional Services Minister Ronald Lamola says COVID-19 preventative measures have been stretched to the limit at correctional facilities in the country and the virus continues to spread. He says this required decisive action. President Cyril Ramaphosa earlier authorised the placement on parole of selected categories of prisoners. Almost 19 000 prisoners will be released on parole to combat the spread of the COVID-19 pandemic in the already overcrowded facilities in the country. Sixty six inmates and 36 officials at correctional facilities in the Eastern Cape have tested positive for the coronavirus. In the Western Cape, 52 officials have tested positive The Ministerâ€™s full briefing is in the video below: 